In the context of the series, the Ice King is a recurring antagonist of the series, and frequently kidnaps princesses throughout Ooo; although he is often at odds with Finn and Jake, he is generally not a serious threat.<ref name=characters>{{cite web|title=Adventure Time {{!}} Characters|url=http://www.cartoonnetwork.com/tv_shows/adventuretime/characters/index.html|publisher=[[Cartoon_Network|CartoonNetwork.com]]|accessdate=January 22, 2013}}</ref> In the [[Adventure_Time_(season_3)|third season]] episode "[[Holly_Jolly_Secrets|Holly Jolly Secrets]]", it is revealed that the Ice King was originally a human archaeologist named Simon Petrikov who, after placing a mysterious ice crown on his head, became crazed with magic and scared off the love of his life, Betty, whom he never saw again.<ref>{{cite episode| title=Holly Jolly Secrets| series=Adventure Time| serieslink=|credits = [[Larry_Leichliter|Larry Leichliter]] (directors); Kent Osborne & Somvilay Xayaphone (writers) | network = [[Cartoon_Network|Cartoon Network]] |airdate=November 28, 2011 | season = 3 | number = 19 & 20}}</ref> In the [[Adventure_Time_(season_4)|fourth season]] episode "[[I_Remember_You_(Adventure_Time)|I Remember You]]", it was revealed that Marceline, a thousand year-old vampire, and the Ice King had originally met following the events of the mysterious Mushroom War, a cataclysmic war that destroyed modern human society, and "[[Simon_&_Marcy|Simon & Marcy]]" revealed that the two by doc"> shared a father-daughter bond.<ref name="I Remember You">{{cite web|url=http://www.avclub.com/articles/i-remember-you,86397/|title='I Remember You' {{!}} Adventure Time {{!}} TV Club|date=October 15, 2012 |publisher=[[The_Onion|The Onion]]|work=[[The_A.V._Club|The A.V. Club]]|author=Oliver Sava|accessdate= October 16, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wizards.com/dnd/Article.aspx?x=dnd/4spot/20110408|title=Dungeons & Dragons Roleplaying Game Official Home Page – Pendleton Ward Interview|publisher=W